                            <comment id="12654172" author="ryantxu" created="Sun, 7 Dec 2008 04:47:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From the discussion, I think we agree the destination source layout should look like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; /src/common  (moved from existing src/java/o.a.s.common)&lt;br/&gt;
 /src/solrj  (moved from client/java)&lt;br/&gt;
 /src/java  (no change)&lt;br/&gt;
 /src/webapp/src  (no change)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unless I hear any objections, i&apos;ll make this change in the next few days...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12654215" author="ryantxu" created="Sun, 7 Dec 2008 16:51:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking over this now....  Something that does not fit nicely is where do we put the &apos;test&apos; classes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For simplicity, I think we should put them all into the existing /src/test/org... tree&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12654225" author="ryantxu" created="Sun, 7 Dec 2008 18:39:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch that moves things around and updates the build.xml file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since SVN patch does not deal well with &apos;svn mv&apos;, the patch is kinda useless, but I post it here for good measure...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;tests pass, and as far as i can tell the maven artifacts look reasonable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12683775" author="shalinmangar" created="Fri, 20 Mar 2009 07:03:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is in trunk now. Marking as resolved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Ryan!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
